<div class="description">
    <h3>Description</h3>

    <div class="body">
        <pre class="highlight"><code>
$object = new SomeObject();
$object-&gt;setChildren( array(new SomeChild, new SomeChild));
</code></pre>

<p>If making {{$form-&gt;bind( $object )}} then Collection element objects are not automatically set, but they have to be set manually.
In MyForm extends Form:</p>

<pre class="highlight"><code>
public function bind( $object, $flags = 17 ) {
    parent::bind( $object );
    foreach( $object-&gt;getRows() as $i =&gt; $row ) {
        $this-&gt;get('Collection')-&gt;get($i)-&gt;setObject( $row );
    }
}
</code></pre>

<p>This probably should work automatically.
In current architecture it is hard to propose a good solution, as bind method only exists in Form. I would probably recommend adding bind method also to fieldsets. (logically objects are kept in Fieldset, so why there can't be bind method?</p>

